gov.nih.nci.codegen
Class Generator

java.lang.Object
  gov.nih.nci.codegen.Generator

public class Generator
extends java.lang.Object

Generates the code from the model. Generator class iterates over available Validator in the validators and reports errors if any discovered. Subsequent to the validation, Generator validates all the Transformer from the transformers list in a sequence. After validating the transformers list, it iterates over all the Transformer in the transformers list to transform the model into desired artifacts.

Generator can exit from execution only for following reasons

  • Errors discovered at the end of the execution of all the Validator contained in the validators list
  • Errors discovered at the end of the execution of validation method of all the Transformer contained in the transformers list
  • Errors discovered at the end of the execution of execute method of all the Transformer contained in the transformers list

Method Detail

execute

public void execute()
Entry point into the Generator after all the configuration is completed by the calling class. The sequence of execution is as follows
  1. Execute all the Validator.validate(UMLModel) instances contained in the validators list.
  2. Report error (if any) discovered by the previous step
  3. Execute gov.nih.nci.codegen.Transformer#validate(UMLModel)) method of the Transformer contained in the transformers list.
  4. Report error (if any) discovered by the previous step
  5. Execute gov.nih.nci.codegen.Transformer#execute(UMLModel)) method of the Transformer contained in the transformers list.
  6. Report error (if any) discovered by the previous step
